'''Matth<U+00E4>us Aurogallus''', also known as ''Matth<U+00E4>us Goldhahn'' ([[1490]] - [[November 10]], [[1543]]) was a German linguist. 

Born in [[Chomutov|Komotau]], [[Bohemia]], he served as Professor of Hebrew at the [[University of Wittenberg]] and was a colleague of [[Philipp Melanchthon]] and [[Martin Luther]]. He assisted Luther in the revision of the reformer's translation of the [[Old Testament]].<ref>Friedrich Wilhelm Bautz, [http://www.bautz.de/bbkl/a/aurogallus_m.shtml "AUROGALLUS (Goldhahn), Matth<U+00E4>us, Hebraist,"] in <cite>Biographisch-Bibliographisches Kirchenlexicon Online</cite> (Nordhausen, Germany:Verlag Traugott Bautz, 2006), 1:304.</ref>

He died at Wittenberg.

== Works ==
*''Hebr<U+00E4>isch und chald<U+00E4>isch Grammatik (1523-25, 1531)
*''Chronik der Herz<U+00F6>ge uund K<U+00F6>nige von B<U+00F6>hmen''
*''Hebr<U+00E4>isch historisch-geographisches Reallexicon'' (1526-1539)

